JMPD's Wayne Minnaar spoke with eNCA's Clement Manyathela. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Johannesburg Metro Police Department is investigating after a video showing officers allegedly harassing a street vendor went viral on social media. It is believed a passer-by captured the incident on his phone. The JMPD's Wayne Minnaar said: "Every aspect concerning the incident is being investigated." Minnaar said City By-Laws are not always adhered to by street vendors.